## Permissions (`src/lib/auth/permissions.ts`)

Pattern: `<module>.view` and `<module>.manage` where applicable. Slugs in TypeScript; **assignments in DB**.

| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `admin_permissions` | Slug, label, category (seeded) |
| `admin_roles` | `super_admin`, `administrator`, `operator` + custom |
| `admin_role_permissions` | Role ↔ permission junction |
| `profiles.admin_role_id` | Panel role per user |

`hasPermissionInSet(permissions, slug, isSuperAdmin)` — super admin bypasses all checks.  
Cache: `getAllAdminRoles()` tag `admin-roles`. Settings matrix invalidates on save.

When adding a permission: seed slug in migration, add to `PERMISSIONS`, `navigation.ts`, messages, **and** `DRIVER_APP_HANDOFF.md` if app-facing.

